    b?
        A transformer works by generating a fluctuating magnetic field around the primary coil which induces a current in the secondary coil. An AC power supply must be used to make the magnetic field fluctuating, as otherwise the there will be no magnetic flux, and there will not be a current induced in the secondary coil. The iron core is used to make the generated magnetic field stronger and hence improve efficiency. A transformer changes output voltage from the input by having more/less turns on the secondary coil than the first, which increases/decreases output voltage.
