        I do not agree with the student's suggestion. While, true, the small spacecraft engine does not provide much acceleration so would not be useful for fast maneuvering, there is little resistance due to friction in space, so the small acceleration, if maintained for a long time, could still cause a great buildup of speed. We can see that the acceleration can be maintained for a long time, because it carries 0.75/(9.9 * 10^-8) = 7575757.5... ~= 7600000 seconds of fuel, so since it can accelerate the craft for a long time, it will be useful.
